const explanationMap = {
  'Afghanistan': 'The Afghan flag features three vertical stripes of black, red, and green with the national emblem centered in white. The emblem includes a mosque, sheaves of wheat, and the shahada (Islamic declaration of faith).',
  'Albania': 'Albania\'s flag shows a black double-headed eagle on a red background. The eagle is a symbol of sovereignty dating to the medieval Albanian lord Gjergj Kastrioti Skanderbeg.',
  'Algeria': 'The Algerian flag is divided vertically with green on the left and white on the right, bearing a red crescent and star at the center. Green and white are traditional Islamic colors, while the crescent and star represent Islam.',
  'Andorra': 'Andorra\'s tricolor flag of blue, yellow, and red vertical stripes bears the national coat of arms in the center. The coat of arms references the co-princes of Andorra: the Bishop of Urgell and the President of France.',
  'Angola': 'Angola\'s flag has horizontal bands of red over black, with a centered emblem of a machete, cogwheel, and star in gold. The design reflects the country\'s Marxist independence movement of 1975.',
  'Antigua and Barbuda': 'The flag features a black background with a rising yellow sun above horizontal bands of blue, white, and red in a V-shape. The rising sun and colors symbolize the dawn of a new era, the sea, and the people.',
  'Argentina': 'Argentina\'s flag has two horizontal blue stripes flanking a white stripe, with a golden "Sun of May" in the center. The sun commemorates the May Revolution of 1810 that began Argentina\'s independence.',
  'Armenia': 'Armenia\'s tricolor of red, blue, and orange horizontal stripes is called the "tricolor." Red represents the Armenian Highland and struggles, blue the sky and people\'s will to live, and orange the creative talent and hardworking nature.',
  'Australia': 'Australia\'s flag features the Union Jack in the upper left, a large Commonwealth Star below it, and the Southern Cross constellation on the right. The Union Jack reflects British heritage, while the stars represent the southern hemisphere location.',
  'Austria': 'Austria\'s simple tricolor of red-white-red horizontal stripes is one of the oldest national flags in the world, dating to the 13th century. Legend says a duke\'s white battle garment was stained red except where his sword belt covered it.',
  'Azerbaijan': 'Azerbaijan\'s flag has horizontal bands of blue, red, and green with a white crescent and eight-pointed star. Blue represents the Turkic heritage, red modernization and democracy, and green Islam.',
  'Bahrain': 'Bahrain\'s flag is red with a white band on the left separated by a serrated edge of five white triangles pointing inward. The five points represent the five pillars of Islam.',
  'Bangladesh': 'Bangladesh\'s flag features a red circle on a green background, slightly off-center toward the hoist. Green represents the lush landscape and the majority Muslim population, while red symbolizes the blood shed for independence.',
  'Barbados': 'The Barbadian flag has vertical stripes of ultramarine and gold flanking a black trident head in the center. The broken trident symbolizes the break from colonial status, while blue and gold represent sea and sand.',
  'Belarus': 'Belarus\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red over green with a traditional Belarusian decorative pattern in red and white on the hoist side. The pattern is derived from traditional folk embroidery.',
  'Belgium': 'Belgium\'s vertical tricolor of black, yellow, and red takes its colors from the arms of the Duchy of Brabant. The vertical orientation was inspired by the French Revolution\'s tricolor.',
  'Belize': 'Belize\'s flag is royal blue with red stripes at top and bottom and a white circle bearing the national coat of arms. The coat of arms shows two woodcutters with a mahogany tree, reflecting the country\'s colonial lumber history.',
  'Benin': 'Benin\'s flag has a vertical green stripe on the hoist side and horizontal yellow over red stripes on the fly side. These Pan-African colors represent the hope of rebirth (green), the country\'s treasure (yellow), and the courage of the ancestors (red).',
  'Bhutan': 'Bhutan\'s striking flag is divided diagonally orange over red-maroon, with a white dragon (Druk) holding jewels across the center. The dragon is the national symbol; orange represents Buddhist practices and red the secular tradition.',
  'Bolivia': 'Bolivia\'s horizontal tricolor of red, yellow, and green bears the national coat of arms in the center. Red represents the blood of brave soldiers, yellow the mineral deposits, and green the fertile land.',
  'Bosnia and Herzegovina': 'The Bosnian flag has a yellow triangle on a blue background with a diagonal row of white stars. The triangle represents the three constituent peoples; blue and yellow reference the European Union colors.',
  'Botswana': 'Botswana\'s flag has a light blue background with a horizontal black stripe bordered by white. Blue represents water and rain; the black and white stripe symbolizes racial harmony.',
  'Brazil': 'Brazil\'s flag features a green field with a large yellow diamond, inside which is a blue celestial globe showing stars and the motto "Ordem e Progresso" (Order and Progress). The globe depicts the night sky over Rio de Janeiro on November 15, 1889.',
  'Brunei': 'Brunei\'s flag is yellow with diagonal black and white stripes and the national coat of arms in red at center. Yellow represents the Sultan, while black and white represent chief ministers.',
  'Bulgaria': 'Bulgaria\'s horizontal tricolor of white, green, and red is similar to Russia\'s but rotated 90 degrees. White represents peace, green represents agriculture, and red represents the valor of soldiers.',
  'Burkina Faso': 'Burkina Faso\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red over green with a five-pointed yellow star in the center. The red represents the revolution and green the country\'s abundance, while the star is a guiding light of the revolution.',
  'Burundi': 'Burundi\'s flag is divided by a white saltire cross into red and green triangles, with a white circle at center containing a red-bordered white circle with three green six-pointed stars. The stars represent the three ethnic groups: Hutu, Tutsi, and Twa.',
  'Cambodia': 'Cambodia\'s flag features horizontal blue-red-blue stripes with a white depiction of the famous Angkor Wat temple complex in the center. Angkor Wat is the world\'s largest religious monument and a symbol of Khmer civilization.',
  'Cameroon': 'Cameroon\'s vertical tricolor of green, red, and yellow bears a gold five-pointed star in the center red stripe. The green represents the forests of the south, red unity, and yellow the savannas of the north.',
  'Canada': 'Canada\'s simple and iconic "Maple Leaf" flag has vertical red stripes flanking a white square bearing a red 11-pointed maple leaf. Adopted in 1965, it replaced a design with the Union Jack.',
  'Cape Verde': 'Cape Verde\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, and red, with a circle of ten yellow five-pointed stars. The stars represent the ten main islands of the archipelago.',
  'Central African Republic': 'The Central African Republic\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, green, and yellow with a red vertical stripe through the center and a gold five-pointed star in the upper left. The vertical red stripe symbolizes the blood shed for independence.',
  'Chad': 'Chad\'s vertical tricolor of blue, yellow, and red is nearly identical to Romania\'s flag except for a slightly different shade of blue. Blue represents the sky and hope, yellow the sun and desert, and red the blood of martyrs.',
  'Chile': 'Chile\'s flag has two horizontal bands of white over red with a blue square in the upper hoist containing a single white star. The star represents a guide to progress and honor; white is for the snow of the Andes, red for the blood of patriots.',
  'China': 'China\'s red flag features a large yellow five-pointed star with four smaller stars arranged in an arc. Red represents the communist revolution; the large star represents the Communist Party, the four small stars represent the classes of Chinese people.',
  'Colombia': 'Colombia\'s horizontal tricolor of yellow, blue, and red has a wide yellow band at top. Yellow represents Colombia\'s gold and fertile land, blue the seas and sky, and red the blood of independence fighters.',
  'Comoros': 'Comoros\'s flag has horizontal stripes of yellow, white, red, and blue with a green triangle at the hoist bearing a white crescent and four white stars. The four stars and stripes represent the four main islands.',
  'Costa Rica': 'Costa Rica\'s flag has five horizontal stripes of blue, white, red (wider), white, and blue. The wide red stripe bears the national coat of arms. The colors were inspired by the French Revolution.',
  'Croatia': 'Croatia\'s horizontal tricolor of red, white, and blue bears the national coat of arms centered on the white stripe. The arms feature a distinctive red and white checkerboard shield, the "šahovnica."',
  'Cuba': 'Cuba\'s flag has five horizontal stripes of blue and white with a red equilateral triangle at the hoist bearing a white five-pointed star. The triangle represents equality, fraternity, and liberty; the star is the "Lone Star" of independence.',
  'Cyprus': 'Cyprus\'s flag is unique: a white background with a copper-orange silhouette of the island and two olive branches below. The design represents peace and the island\'s rich copper deposits (Cyprus was named for copper).',
  'Czech Republic': 'The Czech flag has horizontal white over red stripes with a blue triangle extending from the hoist. The blue wedge was added to distinguish it from the identical Polish flag; the colors derive from the historic lands of Bohemia and Moravia.',
  'Democratic Republic of the Congo': 'The DRC\'s flag is sky blue with a yellow-edged red diagonal stripe from lower hoist to upper fly, and a yellow five-pointed star in the upper left. Blue represents peace, red the blood of martyrs, and the star a bright future.',
  'Denmark': 'Denmark\'s "Dannebrog" is one of the world\'s oldest national flags, dating to at least 1370. A white Nordic cross extends to the edges of a red field, with the vertical bar shifted toward the hoist.',
  'Djibouti': 'Djibouti\'s flag has horizontal stripes of light blue over green with a white equilateral triangle at the hoist bearing a red five-pointed star. Blue represents the sea and sky, green the earth, and the star is a symbol of unity.',
  'Dominica': 'Dominica\'s dark green flag features a centered cross of yellow, black, and white stripes, with a red circle bearing a Sisserou parrot (national bird) surrounded by ten green five-pointed stars. The rare parrot is found only on Dominica.',
  'Dominican Republic': 'The Dominican Republic\'s flag has a white cross dividing red and blue quarters, with the national coat of arms at the center. The coat of arms includes the Bible open to the Gospel of John and six spears.',
  'Ecuador': 'Ecuador\'s horizontal tricolor of yellow, blue, and red bears the national coat of arms in the center, which includes Chimborazo volcano, a river, and a condor. The design is nearly identical to Colombia\'s, distinguished only by the coat of arms.',
  'Egypt': 'Egypt\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and black with the Eagle of Saladin in gold at the center. The Pan-Arab colors and the eagle connect Egypt to Arab unity and the medieval warrior Saladin.',
  'El Salvador': 'El Salvador\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, and blue with the national coat of arms at center. The coat of arms features the date of Central American independence, a rainbow, and five volcanoes.',
  'Equatorial Guinea': 'Equatorial Guinea\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, white, and red with a blue triangle at the hoist and the national coat of arms at center. The arms feature a silk-cotton tree, six six-pointed stars, and a silver shield.',
  'Eritrea': 'Eritrea\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, red, and blue with a gold emblem on the red stripe. The gold olive wreath and branch on the red triangle symbolize peace; the colors represent the country\'s fertility, blood shed in war, and the Red Sea.',
  'Estonia': 'Estonia\'s horizontal tricolor of blue, black, and white is nicknamed the "blue-black-white." Blue represents faith, loyalty, and the sky; black the fertile soil and suffering; white hope, virtue, and snow.',
  'Eswatini': 'Eswatini\'s (formerly Swaziland) flag has horizontal stripes of blue, yellow, and red with a Swazi shield, two spears, and a staff adorned with feathers centered on the red stripe. It is one of Africa\'s most distinctive flags.',
  'Ethiopia': 'Ethiopia\'s horizontal tricolor of green, yellow, and red is the oldest of the Pan-African flags. The centered blue circle with a gold star represents the unity of Ethiopia\'s peoples. Ethiopia inspired many African nations\' flags.',
  'Fiji': 'Fiji\'s light blue flag bears the Union Jack in the upper left and the Fijian coat of arms on the right. The coat of arms shows a British lion holding a cocoa pod, sugar cane, a dove, and a bunch of bananas.',
  'Finland': 'Finland\'s flag is white with a blue Nordic cross. The cross represents Christianity, while blue and white are traditional Finnish colors representing the country\'s numerous lakes and snow.',
  'France': 'The French "tricolore" of vertical blue, white, and red stripes dates from the Revolution of 1789. Blue and red are the traditional colors of Paris, while white represents the monarchy. It became the model for many national flags worldwide.',
  'Gabon': 'Gabon\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, yellow, and blue. Green represents the forest, yellow the equator, and blue the sea.',
  'Georgia': 'Georgia\'s white flag with a large red cross and four smaller red crosses in each quadrant is known as the "Five Cross Flag." It dates to the medieval Kingdom of Georgia and represents Jesus Christ and the four evangelists.',
  'Germany': 'Germany\'s horizontal tricolor of black, red, and gold dates to the Wars of Liberation against Napoleon. These colors come from the uniforms of the Lützow Free Corps. The current flag was adopted by West Germany in 1949.',
  'Ghana': 'Ghana\'s horizontal tricolor of red, gold, and green with a black five-pointed star was adopted at independence in 1957 and inspired other African nations. The star is the "lodestar of African freedom."',
  'Greece': 'Greece\'s flag has nine horizontal stripes of blue and white representing the nine syllables of the independence motto, with a white cross on blue in the upper hoist. The cross represents Greek Orthodox Christianity.',
  'Grenada': 'Grenada\'s flag is divided into gold and green triangles bordered by red with a centered circle. A nutmeg on the left represents Grenada\'s status as the "Isle of Spice," a leading nutmeg producer.',
  'Guatemala': 'Guatemala\'s vertical tricolor of sky blue, white, and sky blue bears the national coat of arms at center. The arms feature a quetzal bird (symbolizing freedom), a rifle, swords, and a laurel wreath.',
  'Guinea': 'Guinea\'s vertical tricolor of red, yellow, and green uses the Pan-African colors in reverse order from Ghana\'s flag. Red represents the blood of martyrs, yellow the gold of the sun, and green the vegetation.',
  'Guinea-Bissau': 'Guinea-Bissau\'s flag has a vertical red stripe with a black star at the hoist, and two horizontal stripes of yellow over green. The colors are Pan-African; the black star represents African unity.',
  'Guyana': 'Guyana\'s flag features a green field with a white-bordered golden arrow pointing from hoist to fly, and a black-bordered red triangle at the hoist. The design, called the "Golden Arrowhead," symbolizes Guyana\'s mineral wealth and forward progress.',
  'Haiti': 'Haiti\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue over red with the national coat of arms on a white panel at the center. The arms show a palm tree with a cannon and cannonballs; the flag was created by removing white from the French tricolor.',
  'Honduras': 'Honduras\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, and blue with five blue five-pointed stars arranged in an X pattern on the white stripe. The stars represent the five members of the Central American Federation.',
  'Hungary': 'Hungary\'s horizontal tricolor of red, white, and green has been used since the 19th century. Red represents strength, white faithfulness, and green hope.',
  'Iceland': 'Iceland\'s flag is blue with a red Nordic cross outlined in white. The colors represent Iceland\'s landscape: the red of volcanic fire, white of ice and snow, and blue of the mountains.',
  'India': 'India\'s "Tiranga" has horizontal stripes of saffron, white, and India green with a navy blue Ashoka Chakra (wheel of law) at the center. The wheel has 24 spokes representing continuous progress.',
  'Indonesia': 'Indonesia\'s "Sang Saka Merah-Putih" (sacred red and white) has two equal horizontal stripes of red over white. The design dates to the Majapahit Empire of the 13th century. It is nearly identical to Monaco\'s flag.',
  'Iran': 'Iran\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, white, and red with the Allah emblem in red at the center. Green borders at the top and bottom bear the phrase "Allahu Akbar" repeated 22 times, marking the date of the Islamic Revolution.',
  'Iraq': 'Iraq\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and black with the phrase "Allahu Akbar" (God is Greatest) in green Kufic script on the white stripe. The Pan-Arab colors connect Iraq to Arab unity.',
  'Ireland': 'Ireland\'s vertical tricolor of green, white, and orange was inspired by the French tricolore. Green represents the Catholic tradition, orange the Protestant tradition, and white the peace between them.',
  'Israel': 'Israel\'s flag features a blue Star of David between two horizontal blue stripes on a white background, resembling a tallit (Jewish prayer shawl). The star is an ancient symbol of Judaism known as the "Shield of David."',
  'Italy': 'Italy\'s vertical tricolor of green, white, and red was inspired by the French Revolution. Napoleon introduced a similar design to the Cisalpine Republic. Green represents the country\'s landscape, white the snow of the Alps, and red the blood of independence fighters.',
  'Ivory Coast': 'Ivory Coast\'s vertical tricolor of orange, white, and green is the mirror image of Ireland\'s flag. Orange represents the savanna regions, white peace and unity, and green hope and forests.',
  'Jamaica': 'Jamaica\'s flag features a gold diagonal cross (saltire) dividing the flag into black triangles at the top and bottom and green triangles at the sides. Black represents hardships, gold natural wealth and sunshine, and green hope and agriculture.',
  'Japan': 'Japan\'s "Hinomaru" (disk of the sun) features a red circle on a white background representing the rising sun. It is one of the world\'s most recognizable flags and has been used in some form since the 12th century.',
  'Jordan': 'Jordan\'s flag has horizontal stripes of black, white, and green with a red triangle at the hoist containing a white seven-pointed star. The star represents the seven verses of Al-Fatihah and the unity of Arab peoples.',
  'Kazakhstan': 'Kazakhstan\'s light blue flag features a golden sun with 32 rays in the upper left, a golden steppe eagle below it, and a vertical ornamental pattern strip along the hoist. Light blue represents the sky and freedom.',
  'Kenya': 'Kenya\'s horizontal tricolor of black, red, and green is overlaid with two white stripes and a Maasai shield with two crossed spears at the center. The shield and spears represent the defense of freedom.',
  'Kiribati': 'Kiribati\'s flag features a red upper half with a golden frigate bird flying over a rising sun, and a blue lower half with three wavy white stripes representing the Pacific Ocean. The 17 rays of the sun represent the 16 Gilbert Islands plus Banaba.',
  'Kosovo': 'Kosovo\'s blue flag shows the outline of the country in gold with six white stars above it representing the six major ethnic groups. It is modeled after the flag of Bosnia and Herzegovina.',
  'Kuwait': 'Kuwait\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, white, and red with a black trapezoid at the hoist. The Pan-Arab colors are used with black representing the battles, white the purity of the people, green the fertile land, and red bloodshed.',
  'Kyrgyzstan': 'Kyrgyzstan\'s red flag features a yellow sun with 40 rays and at the center a representation of the top of a yurt (tunduk). The 40 rays represent the 40 tribes united by the hero Manas.',
  'Laos': 'Laos\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, dark blue, and red with a white circle at the center. The circle represents the moon over the Mekong River. The flag was adopted by the communist Pathet Lao movement.',
  'Latvia': 'Latvia\'s flag features a distinctive dark carmine-red stripe at top and bottom with a white stripe in the middle. The design is one of the world\'s oldest, dating back to 1279 according to legend.',
  'Lebanon': 'Lebanon\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and red with a green cedar tree in the center. The Cedar of Lebanon is a biblical symbol of strength and immortality.',
  'Lesotho': 'Lesotho\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, and green with a black Basotho hat (mokorotlo) at the center. The hat design was updated in 2006 for the 40th independence anniversary.',
  'Liberia': 'Liberia\'s flag closely resembles the United States flag with 11 red and white stripes and a blue square in the upper left containing a single white five-pointed star. The 11 stripes represent the signatories of Liberia\'s Declaration of Independence.',
  'Libya': 'Libya\'s flag is black with a white crescent and star at the center. It was the flag of the Kingdom of Libya and was restored after the fall of Gaddafi in 2011, replacing the all-green flag.',
  'Liechtenstein': 'Liechtenstein\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue over red with a gold crown in the upper hoist. The crown was added in 1937 after Liechtenstein discovered that Haiti had the same flag at the 1936 Olympics.',
  'Lithuania': 'Lithuania\'s horizontal tricolor of yellow, green, and red was historically used in the 20th century. Yellow represents wheat fields and the sun, green the forests and hope, and red love of the homeland and courage.',
  'Luxembourg': 'Luxembourg\'s horizontal tricolor of red, white, and light blue is nearly identical to the Netherlands\' flag but with a lighter blue and different proportions. The colors derive from the coat of arms of the House of Luxembourg.',
  'Madagascar': 'Madagascar\'s flag has a vertical white stripe at the hoist with horizontal red over green stripes. White represents purity, red sovereignty, and green hope. The design reflects the Merina Kingdom\'s traditional colors.',
  'Malawi': 'Malawi\'s flag has horizontal stripes of black, red, and green with a rising red sun at the center of the black stripe. The sunrise represents the dawning of hope and freedom in Africa.',
  'Malaysia': 'Malaysia\'s flag has 14 alternating red and white horizontal stripes with a blue canton bearing a yellow crescent and a 14-pointed star. The 14 stripes and star points represent Malaysia\'s 13 states plus the federal government.',
  'Maldives': 'The Maldivian flag is a green rectangle with a white crescent centered on a red field. Red represents the blood of heroes, green prosperity and peace, and the crescent represents the Islamic faith.',
  'Mali': 'Mali\'s vertical tricolor of green, yellow, and red uses Pan-African colors. Previously it had a black figure representing the human figure, but this was removed. The colors represent the forests (green), purity and mineral wealth (yellow), and blood (red).',
  'Malta': 'Malta\'s flag has vertical stripes of white and red with the George Cross in the upper hoist corner. The George Cross was awarded to Malta by King George VI in 1942 for the island\'s bravery during World War II.',
  'Marshall Islands': 'The Marshall Islands\' flag is navy blue with two diagonal stripes of orange over white rising from the lower hoist, and a white 24-pointed star in the upper hoist. The star represents the Bikini Atoll and other atolls.',
  'Mauritania': 'Mauritania\'s green flag has a gold star and crescent with two horizontal red stripes added in 2017. Green and gold represent Islam, while the red stripes were added to commemorate the blood shed defending the country.',
  'Mauritius': 'Mauritius\'s flag has four equal horizontal stripes of red, blue, yellow, and green. Red represents independence, blue the Indian Ocean, yellow the new light of independence, and green agriculture.',
  'Mexico': 'Mexico\'s vertical tricolor of green, white, and red bears the national coat of arms at the center showing an eagle perched on a cactus devouring a serpent — an Aztec legend marking the site of Tenochtitlan.',
  'Moldova': 'Moldova\'s vertical tricolor of blue, yellow, and red bears the national coat of arms on the yellow stripe. The arms show an eagle holding an olive branch and scepter with a shield depicting an aurochs head.',
  'Monaco': 'Monaco\'s flag has two equal horizontal stripes of red over white. It is the colors of the Grimaldi family who have ruled Monaco since 1297. It is nearly identical to Indonesia\'s flag.',
  'Mongolia': 'Mongolia\'s flag has vertical stripes of red, blue, and red with a gold Soyombo symbol on the left red stripe. The Soyombo is a complex symbol representing freedom, sovereignty, and natural elements.',
  'Montenegro': 'Montenegro\'s flag is red with a gold border and the national coat of arms at the center. The golden eagle holding a scepter and orb reflects the country\'s historical connection to the Byzantine Empire.',
  'Morocco': 'Morocco\'s red flag bears a green interlaced pentagram (the Seal of Solomon) at the center. Red represents hardiness, bravery, strength, and valor; the green star represents Islam and the five pillars of faith.',
  'Mozambique': 'Mozambique\'s flag features horizontal stripes of green, white-edged black, and yellow with a red triangle at the hoist bearing an open book, a hoe, and an AK-47 assault rifle. It is the only current national flag featuring a modern assault rifle.',
  'Myanmar': 'Myanmar\'s flag has horizontal stripes of yellow, green, and red with a large white five-pointed star in the center. The three colors represent solidarity, peace, and courage.',
  'Namibia': 'Namibia\'s flag has a diagonal red stripe bordered by white from the lower hoist to upper fly, with a gold sun in the upper left blue triangle and green in the lower right. The sun represents life and energy.',
  'Nauru': 'Nauru\'s flag has a blue background with a thin gold horizontal stripe representing the equator and a 12-pointed white star below it representing the 12 indigenous tribes of Nauru.',
  'Nepal': 'Nepal\'s flag is the world\'s only non-rectangular national flag, consisting of two stacked triangular pennants. The crimson red flag with blue border features a white moon in the lower pennant and a white sun in the upper. It represents the Himalayan mountains.',
  'Netherlands': 'The Dutch tricolor of red, white, and blue horizontal stripes dates from the Dutch Revolt against Spain (1568–1648). Originally orange, white, and blue, the orange was replaced by red over time. It influenced many flags worldwide.',
  'New Zealand': 'New Zealand\'s flag features the Union Jack in the upper left and four red five-pointed stars with white borders representing the Southern Cross constellation. The stars have fewer points than Australia\'s similar stars.',
  'Nicaragua': 'Nicaragua\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white, and blue with the national coat of arms at center. The arms feature a volcano with a rainbow and the text "República de Nicaragua, América Central."',
  'Niger': 'Niger\'s flag has horizontal stripes of orange, white, and green with an orange circle at the center. Orange represents the Sahara Desert, white purity and innocence, and green hope and fertility.',
  'Nigeria': 'Nigeria\'s vertical tricolor of green, white, and green has no emblem. The two green stripes represent Nigeria\'s forests and natural wealth; white represents peace and unity.',
  'North Korea': 'North Korea\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue, white-edged red (wider), and blue with a white circle bearing a red five-pointed star on the left side of the red stripe. The star represents communism.',
  'North Macedonia': 'North Macedonia\'s flag features a golden sun with eight broadening rays on a red background. The sun represents the "new sun of liberty" described in the national anthem.',
  'Norway': 'Norway\'s flag is red with a white-bordered blue Nordic cross. The cross represents Christianity; the colors are associated with freedom, borrowed from France, the Netherlands, and the United States.',
  'Oman': 'Oman\'s flag has vertical stripes of white, red, and green with the national emblem (two crossed swords and a khanjar dagger) in the upper hoist on the red stripe. The emblem is a traditional symbol of Omani identity.',
  'Pakistan': 'Pakistan\'s flag is dark green with a white vertical stripe at the hoist and a white crescent and star. Green represents Islam and the Muslim majority, while white represents religious minorities.',
  'Palau': 'Palau\'s flag is light blue with a yellow circle slightly off-center toward the hoist. Blue represents the Pacific Ocean, and the gold circle represents the moon, which is culturally important to Palauan traditions.',
  'Palestine': 'The Palestinian flag has horizontal stripes of black, white, and green with a red triangle at the hoist. These are the Pan-Arab colors adopted during the Arab Revolt of 1916–1918.',
  'Panama': 'Panama\'s flag is divided into four quarters alternating white and red, with a blue five-pointed star in the white hoist quarter and a red star in the white fly quarter. Blue represents the Conservative Party and red the Liberal Party.',
  'Papua New Guinea': 'Papua New Guinea\'s flag is divided diagonally with red in the upper hoist and black in the lower fly. A yellow Raggiana bird-of-paradise soars on the red half, while the Southern Cross constellation appears in white on the black half.',
  'Paraguay': 'Paraguay\'s horizontal tricolor of red, white, and blue is unusual in having different emblems on each side. The front shows the national coat of arms (a star with olive and palm branches), while the back shows the treasury seal.',
  'Peru': 'Peru\'s vertical tricolor of red, white, and red bears the national coat of arms at the center. The coat of arms includes a vicuña, a cinchona tree, and a cornucopia. The plain version without the arms is used as the national flag.',
  'Philippines': 'The Philippines\' flag has horizontal stripes of blue over red with a white equilateral triangle at the hoist. Inside the triangle are a golden sun with eight rays representing the first provinces, and three gold stars. When at war, the flag is flown upside down (red on top).',
  'Poland': 'Poland\'s flag has two equal horizontal stripes of white over red. These are the traditional colors of Poland derived from its coat of arms (a white eagle on red). It is simple yet distinct.',
  'Portugal': 'Portugal\'s flag has a vertical green stripe at the hoist (two-fifths) and red (three-fifths), with the national coat of arms centered at the junction. The arms include an armillary sphere and the shield of Portugal.',
  'Qatar': 'Qatar\'s flag is maroon with a broad white vertical stripe at the hoist separated by a serrated edge. Maroon represents the blood shed in wars, and the 9 white points represent Qatar as the 9th member of the Gulf states.',
  'Republic of the Congo': 'The Republic of the Congo\'s flag has a diagonal green stripe from the lower hoist to upper fly with yellow and red bands. Green represents the forests, yellow the friendship and kindness, and red the blood of the country\'s martyrs.',
  'Romania': 'Romania\'s vertical tricolor of blue, yellow, and red is nearly identical to Chad\'s flag. Blue represents liberty, yellow justice, and red fraternity. The colors date to the 1848 revolution.',
  'Russia': 'Russia\'s horizontal tricolor of white, blue, and red was created by Peter the Great in 1696, inspired by the Dutch flag. White represents nobility, blue faithfulness, and red courage. It became the model for Slavic national flags.',
  'Rwanda': 'Rwanda\'s flag has horizontal stripes of blue (wide), yellow, and green with a golden sun with 24 rays in the upper fly. Blue represents happiness and peace, yellow mineral wealth, and green prosperity.',
  'Saint Kitts and Nevis': 'The flag has diagonal stripes of green (upper left) and red (lower right) separated by a black diagonal stripe bordered by yellow. Two white five-pointed stars are on the black stripe. Green represents fertility, red the struggle for freedom, black African heritage, yellow sunshine.',
  'Saint Lucia': 'Saint Lucia\'s flag is sky blue with a golden-yellow triangle bearing a black arrowhead outlined in white. The triangles represent the twin Piton mountains, a UNESCO World Heritage site.',
  'Saint Vincent and the Grenadines': 'The flag has vertical stripes of blue, gold, and green with three green diamonds in a "V" formation on the gold center stripe. The "V" stands for Vincent; the green represents the volcanic island nature.',
  'Samoa': 'Samoa\'s flag is red with a blue canton bearing the Southern Cross constellation in white with one four-pointed and four five-pointed stars. Red represents courage, blue freedom, and white purity.',
  'San Marino': 'San Marino\'s flag has horizontal stripes of white over light blue with the national coat of arms at center. The arms show three towers on a mountain. White represents snow on Mount Titano; blue represents the sky.',
  'São Tomé and Príncipe': 'The flag has horizontal stripes of green, yellow, and green (wider) with a red triangle at the hoist and two black five-pointed stars. The stars represent the two main islands. Pan-African colors represent the tropical climate.',
  'Saudi Arabia': 'Saudi Arabia\'s green flag bears the Shahada (Islamic declaration of faith) in white Arabic script: "There is no god but Allah, and Muhammad is the messenger of Allah." Below is a white horizontal sword. Green represents Islam.',
  'Senegal': 'Senegal\'s vertical tricolor of green, yellow, and red with a green star in the yellow stripe resembles Mali\'s flag but with the star added. The star represents the hope of the Senegalese people.',
  'Serbia': 'Serbia\'s horizontal tricolor of red, blue, and white bears a small coat of arms (a crowned eagle with a red shield bearing a cross with four Cs/fleurs-de-lis) on the left side. The colors are pan-Slavic.',
  'Seychelles': 'Seychelles\' flag features five oblique radiating stripes of blue, yellow, red, white, and green emanating from the bottom left corner. No other national flag has a similar radiating design. Each color represents an aspect of the nation.',
  'Sierra Leone': 'Sierra Leone\'s horizontal tricolor of green, white, and blue represents agriculture (green), unity and justice (white), and the Atlantic coast (blue). It was adopted at independence in 1961.',
  'Singapore': 'Singapore\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red over white with a white crescent moon and five white stars arranged in a circle on the red half. Red represents universal brotherhood, white purity. The five stars represent democracy, peace, progress, justice, and equality.',
  'Slovakia': 'Slovakia\'s horizontal tricolor of white, blue, and red is overlaid with the Slovak coat of arms — a white double cross on a blue mound on a red shield — positioned slightly left of center.',
  'Slovenia': 'Slovenia\'s horizontal tricolor of white, blue, and red bears the national coat of arms in the upper hoist. The arms show a blue-outlined Mount Triglav in white on a blue background with two wavy blue lines and three golden stars.',
  'Solomon Islands': 'The Solomon Islands\' flag has a blue upper triangle and green lower triangle separated by a thin yellow diagonal stripe, with five white five-pointed stars in the upper triangle. The stars represent the five main island groups.',
  'Somalia': 'Somalia\'s light blue flag bears a white five-pointed star at the center. The UN-inspired blue represents the sky; the star\'s five points represent the five regions where Somalis traditionally lived.',
  'South Africa': 'South Africa\'s distinctive "Y" flag features a horizontal "Y" shape in green and gold, with black at the hoist, red and blue at the top and bottom, and white borders. Adopted in 1994, it represents the unity of diverse peoples.',
  'South Korea': 'South Korea\'s "Taegukgi" features a white background with a red and blue yin-yang symbol (taeguk) at center and four black trigrams at the corners. The trigrams represent heaven, water, earth, and fire.',
  'South Sudan': 'South Sudan\'s flag has horizontal stripes of black, red, and green with white borders and a blue triangle at the hoist bearing a gold star. Adopted in 2011, the colors represent the people (black), blood (red), hope (green), and peace (white).',
  'Spain': 'Spain\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, yellow (wider), and red with the national coat of arms slightly left of center. The coat of arms includes the shields of Castile, León, Aragon, and Navarre, plus the Pillars of Hercules.',
  'Sri Lanka': 'Sri Lanka\'s flag features a golden lion holding a sword on a dark red background, bordered by gold, with green and orange vertical stripes at the hoist. The lion flag dates to the 5th century BC; the stripes represent Tamil (orange) and Moorish (green) communities.',
  'Sudan': 'Sudan\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and black with a green triangle at the hoist. The Pan-Arab colors represent the blood of martyrs, peace and optimism, and the dark days of oppression.',
  'Suriname': 'Suriname\'s flag has horizontal stripes of green, white, red (wider), white, and green with a gold five-pointed star at the center. Green represents hope and fertility, white justice and freedom, red progress and love. The star represents unity.',
  'Sweden': 'Sweden\'s flag is blue with a yellow Nordic cross extending to the edges. The cross represents Christianity; blue and gold are the traditional Swedish heraldic colors since the Middle Ages.',
  'Switzerland': 'Switzerland\'s flag is the only square national flag other than the Vatican\'s. It is red with a bold white cross. The design dates to 1339 and the cross became the international Red Cross symbol (colors inverted) in 1864.',
  'Syria': 'Syria\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and black with two green five-pointed stars on the white stripe. The Pan-Arab colors with green stars representing Syria and Egypt date to the United Arab Republic of 1958.',
  'São Tomé and Príncipe': 'The flag has horizontal stripes of green, yellow, and green (wider) with a red triangle at the hoist and two black five-pointed stars. The stars represent the two main islands.',
  'Taiwan': 'Taiwan\'s "Blue Sky, White Sun, and a Wholly Red Earth" flag has a red field with a blue canton bearing a white sun with 12 rays. The twelve rays represent the 12 months of the year.',
  'Tajikistan': 'Tajikistan\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white (wider), and green with the national coat of arms centered on the white stripe. The crown and seven stars represent the country\'s sovereignty; colors symbolize purity, unity, and agricultural lands.',
  'Tanzania': 'Tanzania\'s flag has a green upper triangle and blue lower triangle separated by a diagonal black stripe bordered by yellow from the lower hoist to upper fly. Green represents the land, blue the Indian Ocean, black the people, and yellow mineral wealth.',
  'Thailand': 'Thailand\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, blue (wider), white, and red. Known as the "Trairanga," it was introduced in 1917. Red represents the nation, white represents religion, and blue represents the monarch.',
  'The Bahamas': 'The Bahamas\' flag has horizontal stripes of aquamarine, gold, and aquamarine with a black equilateral triangle at the hoist. Aquamarine represents the sea, gold the golden beaches, and black the strength of the Bahamian people.',
  'The Gambia': 'The Gambia\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, blue (with thin white borders), and green. Red represents the sun, blue the Gambia River, and green the land. The blue stripe is narrow, representing the river\'s path through the country.',
  'Timor-Leste': 'Timor-Leste\'s flag has a red background with a black triangle at the hoist bearing a white five-pointed star, and a yellow triangle over that. Red represents liberation, black the history of oppression, and yellow the traces of colonialism.',
  'Togo': 'Togo\'s flag has five horizontal stripes alternating green and yellow with a red canton bearing a white five-pointed star. The five stripes represent Togo\'s five regions; the star represents hope and purity.',
  'Tonga': 'Tonga\'s red flag has a white canton in the upper left bearing a red cross. The cross represents Christianity, which is central to Tongan culture. The red represents Christ\'s blood.',
  'Trinidad and Tobago': 'Trinidad and Tobago\'s flag is red with a white-bordered black diagonal stripe from the upper hoist to the lower fly. Black represents dedication, red the vitality of the people, and white equality.',
  'Tunisia': 'Tunisia\'s red flag bears a white circle at the center containing a red crescent and five-pointed star. The crescent and star represent Islam; the design resembles the Ottoman Empire\'s flag under which Tunisia was once a protectorate.',
  'Turkey': 'Turkey\'s "Ay Yıldız" (crescent star) flag is red with a white crescent and five-pointed star. The Ottoman crescent and star have been used since at least the 18th century. Red represents the blood of Ottoman soldiers.',
  'Turkmenistan': 'Turkmenistan\'s flag is green with a vertical stripe of five traditional carpet guls (medallions) at the hoist and a white crescent with five white stars. The elaborate carpet designs reflect Turkmen weaving traditions.',
  'Tuvalu': 'Tuvalu\'s flag is light blue with the Union Jack in the upper left and nine yellow five-pointed stars representing the nine atolls of the archipelago. The blue represents the Pacific Ocean.',
  'Uganda': 'Uganda\'s flag has six equal horizontal stripes alternating black, yellow, and red, with a white circle at the center bearing a grey crowned crane (national bird). The crane\'s raised leg symbolizes Uganda moving forward.',
  'Ukraine': 'Ukraine\'s flag has equal horizontal stripes of blue over yellow. Blue represents the sky and yellow the wheat fields of the Ukrainian steppe. It dates to the Ukrainian People\'s Republic of 1918.',
  'United Arab Emirates': 'The UAE\'s flag has vertical stripes of green, white, and black from left to right with a horizontal red stripe on the hoist side. The Pan-Arab colors represent the fertile land (green), peace (white), petroleum wealth (black), and unity (red).',
  'United Kingdom': 'The Union Jack combines the crosses of St. George (England — red cross on white), St. Andrew (Scotland — white diagonal cross on blue), and St. Patrick (Ireland — red diagonal cross on white). It has been used since 1801.',
  'United States of America': 'The US flag has 13 alternating red and white stripes representing the original 13 colonies, and a blue canton with 50 white five-pointed stars representing the current 50 states. The current design dates to 1960 when Hawaii was admitted.',
  'Uruguay': 'Uruguay\'s flag has nine horizontal stripes of white and blue with a white canton bearing the "Sun of May." The sun matches Argentina\'s flag, reflecting shared independence history. The nine stripes represent nine original departments.',
  'Uzbekistan': 'Uzbekistan\'s flag has horizontal stripes of sky blue, white, and green separated by thin red lines. A white crescent and 12 white stars are on the blue stripe. Blue represents sky and water, white peace and purity, green nature.',
  'Federated States of Micronesia': 'The Federated States of Micronesia\'s flag is light blue with four white five-pointed stars arranged in a diamond pattern. The blue represents the Pacific Ocean, and the four stars represent the four states: Chuuk, Pohnpei, Kosrae, and Yap.',
  'Vanuatu': 'Vanuatu\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red over green separated by a black horizontal stripe with a yellow Y-shape overlaid. At the hoist is a black triangle bearing a boar\'s tusk threaded with two crossed fern fronds.',
  'Vatican City': 'Vatican City\'s square flag has vertical stripes of gold and white with the papal coat of arms on the white half. The gold and silver represent the keys of Saint Peter; the flag is one of only two square national flags.',
  'Venezuela': 'Venezuela\'s horizontal tricolor of yellow, blue, and red has eight white five-pointed stars in a curved formation on the blue stripe and the national coat of arms on the yellow stripe. The stars represent the original provinces.',
  'Vietnam': 'Vietnam\'s flag is a red field with a large yellow five-pointed star at the center. Red represents the revolution and communist ideology; the star\'s five points represent workers, peasants, soldiers, intellectuals, and youth.',
  'Yemen': 'Yemen\'s flag has horizontal stripes of red, white, and black using Pan-Arab colors. It was created by combining the flags of North Yemen and South Yemen after reunification in 1990.',
  'Zambia': 'Zambia\'s flag is green with an orange eagle in flight in the lower right and vertical stripes of red, black, and orange in the lower right corner. Green represents the natural resources, red freedom, black the people, and orange mineral wealth.',
  'Zimbabwe': 'Zimbabwe\'s flag has seven horizontal stripes of green, yellow, red, black, red, yellow, and green with a white triangle at the hoist bearing a red five-pointed star and a Zimbabwe Bird (stylized soapstone bird). The bird is modeled on ancient ruins.',
};

